x4freetext: .The Energy was Determined by
Use of the Energy Loss Tables of Northcliffe, Nuclear
Data Tables A7,233,70. The Relative Measurement Ofthe
Beam Intensity was Calibrated with a Faraday Cup.
.Alice Accelerator at Orsay
The Overall Uncertainty of the Cross Sections
Excluding the Uncertainty of the Alpha Branching
Ratios is Estimated As 20-25 %.  The Uncertainty in
The Beam Intensity Calibration Amounted to 10-15 %.
The Relative Cross Sections Obtained by the He-Jet
Technique were Converted to Absolute Values by Adopting
A Cross Section of 115(+-20) Mb For the Reaction
Sn-118(AR,5N)Er-153 at a Projectile Energy of 195 MeV.
This Reference Cross Section was Determined Using
Conventional Measurement of Recoils in Al Catcher
Foils. The Number of Er-153 Atoms was Determined Via
The Alpha-Decay of the Granddaughter Tb-149. Thus a
Bombarding Energy of 195 MeV was Chosen to Avoid the
Direct Formation of Either Dy-149 or Tb-149. This is
Correct For the Reactions Sn-118(AR,2P7N)Dy-149 and
Sn-118(AR,3P6N)Tb-149, But It May be Doubtful in the
Cases of Sn-118(AR,A5N)Dy-149 or Sn-118(AR,AP4N)Tb-149
- Comment by the Compiler-.
The Figures from Which the Cross Sections were Taken
Give the Sum of the Projectile Energy and of the
Difference Between the Q-Values of the Reaction in
Question and the Corresponding Reaction with Sn-118
As Target Nuclide. This Difference, not Given in the
Publication was Obtained from Landolt-Boernstein, New
Series, Group1,Vol.5a(1973).
Due to the Lack of the Reaction and Decay Data the
Cross Sections For the Reactions (AR,11N) And (AR,P11N)
Given in the Figures Could not be Entered.
- Comment by the Compiler-.
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Lower Case. Reaction Lines are Corrected.
